properties.Name: StoreFloor
properties.Description:
A grocery store/department row is divided into Shelves that are stored at tier level.

Tier is the height of the location (shelf or bin) from floor level, measured in storage locations where the floor is tier 1 (not 0).

The level above ground of the shelf or bin.

Columns.Name: StoreId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Store.

Columns.Name: FloorId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Floor.

Columns.Name: TotalFloorSpace
Columns.Description: The total floor space of the floor measured in the unit of measure specified by the Unit of Measure ID.
